commitResults.messageTitle: Add Match Feature to Developer and User Guide (#130)
commitResults.messageBody:
* Add Match Implementation to Developer Guide

* Edit user guide

* Fix typo in user guide

* Edit Introduction and Features Sections

* Create MatchCommandParser to parse MatchCommands

MatchCommands are meant to match patients to suitable donors
in the system.

* Add function to parse match commands

* Add skeleton of MatchCommand

* Add matching functionality to MatchCommand

This is an intermediate implementation of MatchCommand, which
is executed to match a patient with Donors in the Donor pool.
Currently when this command is executed, it displays all donors which
matches the specified patient.

Currently in this implementation, a match happens when patient and donor's
blood types are compatible and they pass the tissue typing test.

* Modify AddressBook.java to find and return Patient

* Retrieves specified Patient from PersonList

* Add blood type tests

* Add tissue typing tests

* Fix broken build

* Make edits based on PR Review

* Add unit test for MatchCommand

* Update PersonList with Match Results

* Render MatchCard to display matches

* Store results of matches

* Add NumberOfMatches to track matches of Patients

* Edit PersonListPanel to display matches

* Add MatchedDonor to represent matching donors

* Add MatchedPatient to represent number of matches

A MatchedPatient contains a Patient's details and the number
of matching donors with the Patient

* Edit Donor and Patient match result details

Previously, match results are stored in the Donor and Patient class.
With this commit, match results are no longer stored in
Donor and Patient classes, but are stored in MatchedDonor
and MatchedPatient classes.

* Change PersonListPanel for MatchCommands

Previously, matches and people were stored in the Logic's
filteredPersonsList. This resulted in bugs when rendering the
matches and people.

The solution is to create a separate list to store matches. The
MainWindow will select the list to display.

* Add a new list to store matches

* Add Matching functionality

The changes support matching individual Patients and all Patients

commitResults.messageTitle: Change dummy data to be populated (#157)
commitResults.messageBody: Dummy data created when a person first uses ORGANice is changed.

* Edit diagrams given in existing AB3 Guide

* Improve explanation of match feature

Changes to the explanation are as follows:
* Discuss different aspects in the Logic, UI and Model section.
* Include code snippets for better understanding

To Do:
* Add sequence diagrams
* Add class diagrams
* Expand on design considerations

* Edit developer guide

* Add more messages detailing result of each match

Previously there were only messages detailing if
the command succeeded or failed.

Now some new types of messages are added:
- If the command matches a specific patient, the message
details which patient was matched with all donors.
- If no matches were found, the resulting message states that.
- Messages to provide details on how many matches, and for which patient

* Beautify UI of displayed matches

The following changes were made to the UI:
* Success rate is to be displayed in 2 decimal places instead of one long string
* Match results to be displayed in red
* Nric of patient and donor to be prefixed with "Nric: " followed
by the NRIC of the person.

* Create new ModelStub for testing

Previously a private ModelStub class was created for both AddCommandTest
and MatchCommandTest. This resulted in duplication of code whenever the
Model implementation changed.

This ModelStub class will now be used by all classes, removing the duplication
of code.
